-- Sub-Sahara Africa Stocks: Dangote Flour; First Bank of Nigeria
-- B y   C h r i s   K a y
-- 2012-01-05T16:31:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-05/sub-sahara-africa-stocks-dangote-flour-first-bank-of-nigeria.html
The  FTSE/Namibia Overall Index (FTN098) 
dropped 1.1 percent to 861.08 in Windhoek.  Kenya’s  All-Share Index (NSEASI)  rose 0.5 percent to 54.90 in
Nairobi. Mauritius’s  SEMDEX Index (SEMDEX)  gained for a third day,
climbing 0.1 percent to 1,891.56 by the end of trading. The
 Nigerian Stock Exchange All-Share Index (NGSEINDX)  climbed 0.1 percent to
20,657 in Lagos, according to an e-mailed statement from the
bourse.  Dangote Flour Mills Plc (DANGFLOU)  , a Nigerian producer,
surged 4.9 percent to 5.75 naira, the highest since Nov. 18,
after the Lagos-based company said it expects profit to increase
78 percent during the fourth quarter of its 2011 fiscal year.  First Bank of Nigeria Plc (FIRSTBAN)  , the nation’s
third-largest lender by market value, jumped 2.3 percent, the
most since Dec. 21, to 9 naira after  Standard & Poor’s  revised
its outlook on  Nigeria ’s three biggest banks to positive after
making the same revision to the country last week.  Guaranty Trust Bank Plc (GUARANTY)  , Nigeria’s largest
bank by market value, gained for the first day in three,
increasing 1.4 percent to 14.2 naira, the highest since Dec. 30.  To contact the reporter on this story:
